the vehicle's electrical system is prone to short circuits

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Premature Piston Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature piston failure can cause engine damage, leading to loss of power, coolant, and oil leaks, which can result in engine failure, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
Head gasket failure can cause engine coolant and oil leaks, leading to engine damage, overheating, and loss of power, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Turbo failure can cause loss of power, engine damage, and decreased fuel efficiency, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Valve failure can cause engine damage, leading to loss of power, coolant, and oil leaks, which can result in engine failure, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
The sudden failure and separation of the driveshaft can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and damage to other vehicles, as well as injuries to occupants and other road users.
